{{Moroccan literature}}
'''Abu Mohammed Abd as-Salam al-Qadiri''' (1648‚Äì1698) was an historian and genealogist of the [[Sharif]]ian families of [[Morocco]]. He was the grandfather and precursor of the historian [[Mohammed al-Qadiri]] (1713‚Äì80).<ref name="MeisamiStarkey1998">{{cite book|author1=Julie Scott Meisami|author2=Paul Starkey|title=Encyclopedia of Arabic literature|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=DbCFBX6b3eEC&pg=PA548|accessdate=4 February 2012|year=1998|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-0-415-18572-1|page=627}}</ref> He wrote a book about Ahmad ibn Abdullah al-Ma'n al-Andalusi, entitled ''Al-Maksad al-ahmad fi l-tarif bi-Sayyidina Ibn Abd Allah''.<ref name="AyalonSharon1986">{{cite book|author1=David Ayalon|authorlink1=David Ayalon|author2=[[Moshe Sharon]] |title=Studies in Islamic history and civilization: in honour of Professor David Ayalon|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0_wUAAAAIAAJ|accessdate=4 February 2012|year=1986|publisher=BRILL|isbn=978-965-264-014-7|page=350}}</ref> He was an expert in the field of [[lexicography]], logic, [[rhetoric]], and [[hadith]].

