'''Frederik Christiaan Woudhuizen''' (born 13 February 1959) is an independent scholar who studies ancient Indo-European languages, hieroglyphic Luvian/Luwian, and Mediterranean protohistory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.zmescience.com/science/history-science/stone-inscription-troy-42342/|title=Obscure 3,200-year-old stone inscription finally gets deciphered -- tells of Troy prince conquests and 'Sea People'|date=10 October 2017|website=Zmescience.com|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref> He is the former editor of ''Talanta, Proceedings of the Dutch Archaeological and Historical Society''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://luwianstudies.org/interview-fred-woudhuizen-question-whether-hieroglyphic-inscription-beykoy-might-forged/|title=Interview with Fred Woudhuizen about the question whether the hieroglyphic inscription from Beyk√∂y might be forged - Luwian Studies|date=16 October 2017|website=Luwianstudies.org|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.woudhuizen.nl/fred/|title=Fred Woudhuizen|website=Woudhuizen.nl|accessdate=30 December 2017}}</ref>
==Selected publications== * ''Luwian hieroglyphic monumental rock and stone inscriptions from the Hittite Empire period'' * ''Selected Luwian hieroglyhic texts 1'' * ''Selected Luwian hieroglyhic texts 2'' * ''Selected Luwian hieroglyhic texts, the extended version'' * ''The earliest Cretan scripts'' * ''The earliest Cretan scripts 2'' * ''The Phaistos Disc: A Luwian letter to Nestor'' * ''[http://www.woudhuizen.nl/fred/downloads/2006_The_Ethnicity_of_the_Sea_Peoples,Woudhuizen,F.C..pdf The ethnicity of the Sea Peoples]'' * ''Ethnicity in Mediterranean Protohistory'', with Wim M.J. van Binsbergen * ''Etruscan as a colonial Luwian language'' * ''The Liber Linteus''
