'''Kanchan Pande''' (born 1958) is an Indian [[Isotope geology|Isotope geologist]], [[geochronologist]] and a professor at the department of earth sciences of the [[Indian Institute of Technology Mumbai]].<ref name="Kanchan Pande on IITB">{{Cite web |url=http://www.geos.iitb.ac.in/index.php/kp |title=Kanchan Pande on IITB |date=2016 |publisher=Indian Institute of Technology, Mumbai}}</ref> He is known for his studies on the evolution of continental flood [[basalts]] in the Indian subcontinent<ref name="Brief Profile of the Awardee">{{Cite web |url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/content/Detail.aspx?AID=223 |title=Brief Profile of the Awardee |date=2016 |publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize |access-date=12 November 2016}}</ref> and is an elected fellow of the [[National Academy of Sciences, India]].<ref name="NASI fellows">{{Cite web|url=http://www.nasi.org.in/Year%20Book%202015.pdf |title=NASI fellows |date=2016 |publisher=National Academy of Sciences, India |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150806211716/http://www.nasi.org.in/Year%20Book%202015.pdf |archivedate=2015-08-06 |df= }}</ref> The [[Council of Scientific and Industrial Research]], the apex agency of the Government of India for scientific research, awarded him the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize for Science and Technology]], one of the highest Indian science awards for his contributions to Earth, Atmosphere, Ocean and Planetary Sciences in 2003.<ref name="View Bhatnagar Awardees">{{cite web | url=http://ssbprize.gov.in/Content/AwardeeList.aspx | title=View Bhatnagar Awardees | publisher=Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize | date=2016 | accessdate=12 November 2016}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Long link - please select award year to see details}}

== Biography ==
[[File:Gujarat University Tower Building.jpg|thumb|left|235px|Gujarat University]]
[[File:Western-Ghats-Matheran.jpg|thumb|235px|Deccan Traps]]
Kanchan Pande, born on 14 March 1958 in the Indian state of [[Uttaranchal]], completed his master's degree in geology at [[Kumaun University]] in 1981 and secured PhD in Geochronology and Isotope geology from [[Gujarat University]] in 1990.<ref name="Faculty profile - Academics">{{Cite web |url=http://www.geos.iitb.ac.in/index.php/en/kp-academics |title=Faculty profile - Academics |date=2016 |publisher=Department of Earth Sciences - IIT Mumbai}}</ref> His career started at [[Physical Research Laboratory]] in 1990 as a scientist (Grade D) and he held the position of an associate professor from 1998 to 2002 before becoming a professor in 2003. However, his service as a professor at PRL lasted only 5 months and in June 2003, he moved to the [[Indian Institute of Technology Mumbai]] as a professor at the department of earth sciences and holds the post till date.<ref name="Faculty profile - Career">{{Cite web |url=http://www.geos.iitb.ac.in/index.php/en/kp-positions |title=Faculty profile - Career |date=2016 |publisher=Department of Earth Sciences - IIT Mumbai}}</ref>

Pande is known to have done extensive research on the geochronology of the region covering the [[Deccan Traps]].<ref name="Why save the rocks of the Deccan Plateau?">{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/sci-tech/science/why-save-the-rocks-of-the-deccan-plateau/article7855580.ece |title=Why save the rocks of the Deccan Plateau? |date=8 November 2015 |publisher=The Hindu}}</ref> His researches are reported to have assisted in understanding the ''geochronological constraints for the evolution of continental flood basalts in the Indian subcontinent'' and highlighted their geological and geochemical impact<ref name="Brief Profile of the Awardee" /> which has been detailed in an article, ''Age and duration of the Deccan Traps, India: A review of radiometric and paleomagnetic constraints'', published in June 2002.<ref name="Age and duration of the Deccan Traps, India: A review of radiometric and paleomagnetic constraints">{{Cite journal |last=Kanchan Pande |title=Age and duration of the Deccan Traps, India: A review of radiometric and paleomagnetic constraints |url=https://www.prl.res.in/~library/Pande_K_2002_abst.pdf |journal=Proc. Indian Acad. Sci. (Earth Planet. Sci.) |publication-date=June 2002 |volume=111 |issue=2 |pages=115‚Äì123}}</ref> His studies have been documented in several peer-reviewed articles;<ref name="Publications on IAS">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ias.ac.in/listing/bibliography/jess/Kanchan_Pande |title=Publications on IAS |date=2016 |publisher=Indian Academy of Sciences}}</ref>{{Refn|group=note|Please see ''Selected bibliography'' section}} [[ResearchGate]], an online repository of scientific articles, has listed 70 of them.<ref name="On ResearchGate">{{Cite web |url=https://www.researchgate.net/researcher/73591043_Kanchan_Pande |title=On ResearchGate |date=2016 |publisher=ResearchGate}}</ref>

== Awards and honors ==
Pande, who was selected as Young Associate of the [[Indian Academy of Sciences]] in 1987,<ref name="Faculty profile - Awards">{{Cite web |url=http://www.geos.iitb.ac.in/index.php/en/kp-awards |title=Faculty profile - Awards |date=2016 |publisher=Department of Earth Sciences - IIT Mumbai}}</ref> received the Young Scientist Medal of the [[Indian National Science Academy]] in 1989.<ref name="Young Scientist Medal">{{Cite web |url=http://insaindia.res.in/youngmedal.php |title=Young Scientist Medal |date=2016 |publisher=Indian National Science Academy}}</ref> The [[Council of Scientific and Industrial Research]] awarded him the [[Shanti Swarup Bhatnagar Prize]], one of the highest Indian science awards in 2003.<ref name="Earth Sciences">{{Cite web|url=http://www.csir.res.in/External/Heads/career/award/BPRIZE/Earth_SCIENCES.htm |title=Earth Sciences |date=2016 |publisher=Council of Scientific and Industrial Research |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303200915/http://www.csir.res.in/external/heads/career/award/BPRIZE/Earth_SCIENCES.htm |archivedate=2016-03-03 |df= }}</ref> The [[National Academy of Sciences, India]] elected him as a fellow in 2015.<ref name="NASI fellows" />

